# Project rules

**Before any code change, read `PROJECT_CONTEXT.md` at repo root.** It is the source of truth.

## Stack (active only)

- React 19 + Vite + Tailwind 4 in `src/`
- Express + raw `mssql` in `server.ts` (not `Backend/` .NET or `Frontend/` Angular unless asked)

## Must follow

- Reuse `dataService` / `authService` — no new axios clients per page
- Domain types in `src/types.ts`; camelCase in UI, map DB columns via `COLUMN_MAP` in `server.ts`
- New tables: update `Database/schema.sql`, `TABLE_MAP`, and `COLUMN_MAP` together
- UI: Tailwind + `vibrant-card`, `sonner` toasts, `lucide-react` icons, `motion` for overlays — match `Layout.tsx` / existing pages
- Role gates: update `App.tsx` routes and `Layout.tsx` `menuItems` when adding admin features
- Prefer extending dedicated routes in `server.ts` over duplicating generic CRUD when joins/transactions are needed

## Avoid

- Editing `node_modules`, `dist`, legacy `Frontend/` unless migration task
- Introducing ORMs, new state libraries, or parallel API layers
- Drive-by refactors; no new markdown unless requested
- Assuming JWT protects API — auth is client-side today; do not rely on server middleware that does not exist

## Key files

| Area | Files |
|------|--------|
| API/DB | `server.ts` |
| Routes/UI | `src/App.tsx`, `src/pages/*` |
| HTTP | `src/services/dataService.ts` |
| Types | `src/types.ts` |
| Schema | `Database/schema.sql` |

## Run

`npm run dev` — single process serves `/api` and the SPA.
